{"profile":{"awsPrograms":[{"category":"Serverless Hero","joinedAt":2024.0,"memberStatus":"ACTIVE","programName":"HERO"}],"basicInfo":{"alias":"serverlessadvocate","avatar":"https://avatars.builderprofile.aws.dev/2xwBlq1JoMa6RYvf0giNvUl6Kdg.webp","bio":"Lee Gilmore is an AWS Serverless Hero from the UK who specialises in event-driven architectures, the AWS CDK, domain-driven design, and clean code.\n\nLee is also an international speaker, lead architect, writer, OSS contributor, and engineer, with a passion for building enterprise-grade scalable serverless architectures in the cloud, and building high-performing teams based on trust, vision, and empathy.\n\nLee is also the owner of the Serverless Patterns registry with over 100 free open source solutions and detailed articles: https://www.serverlessadvocate.com/patterns and runs a weekly Serverless newsletter: https://serverlessadvocate.substack.com/\n\nLee also owns https://cloud-cards.com/ which allows users to do micro-learning in their own time, across the categories: software patterns, CICD, engineering, and domain-driven design.","builderProfileId":"12dda6d0-a47d-4135-b12f-70ebc95a223e","createdOn":1.707065344E12,"isStaff":false,"name":"Lee Gilmore (Serverless Hero)"},"location":{},"profileStatus":"ACTIVE","socials":{"blog":"https://www.serverlessadvocate.com/","github":"leegilmorecode","linkedIn":"lee-james-gilmore/","twitter":"LeeJamesGilmore","youtube":"@serverlessadvocate"}}}